                <p>
                  Ground Penetrating Radar (GPR) works by sending pulses of
                  different frequencies into the ground and measuring the return
                  of reflected signals. Structures beneath the surface return a
                  different signal from surrounding materials due to differences
                  in material permittivity.
                </p>
                <p>
                  This technology is ideal for locating non-conductive materials
                  or utility objects, conducting surveys over large areas for
                  indicative detection of possible underground assets in areas
                  without existing records. Geometricus employs a range of
                  different GPR solutions depending on the application.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Our leading GPR, IDS StreamUP, in combination with IQMaps
                  software, provides incredible results in all areas. For
                  hard-to-reach places, we use a GPR system on an unmanned
                  aerial vehicle.
                </p>
